# Treat bundled skill content as vendored so github-linguist does not
# misdetect the project's main language. Files under catalog/ ship with
# ezskills as LLM context (SKILL.md, reference code, snippets) and are
# not part of ezskills' own source. Without this, vendored Ruby in some
# skills (e.g. the Stripe Ruby SDK inside generating-sorbet) makes
# GitHub report Ruby as the dominant language of the repo.
catalog/** linguist-vendored
